      "content": "That's a good start. I want to focus more on the \"social stability\" aspect. It's kind of hard for my classmates to get the logic, so I need more depth. Can you expand on the specific idea that integration causes social friction or instability? Like, what were the historical arguments that suggested mixed-race neighborhoods or integrated schools actually lead to more conflict or a breakdown in community's social cohesion? I need to be able to present these points as logical, rational arguments rather than just \"bad ideas.\"",
